# Audit Trail — {{team_name}}

> What gets logged + the JSONL schema + retention policy. The build
> session implements this contract; tests assert on log shape.

## Scope

Every tool call by every agent gets one log line. Plus key lifecycle
events (wake start, wake end, escalation, approval request, approval
response, kill-switch fire). Append-only. PII redacted before emission.

This contract supports compliance posture (GDPR Article 30 record of
processing) and forensic debugging when the team misbehaves.

## Schema (12-field JSONL)

Every line is a single JSON object with these fields:

```json
{
  "timestamp": "2026-04-28T14:32:11.123Z",
  "correlation_id": "cron-20260428T143000Z-a3f21b",
  "agent_id": "{{example_agent_id}}",
  "wake_id": "wake-20260428T143000Z-a3f21b",
  "action": "tool_call",
  "tool": "mcp__gmail__search_messages",
  "args_summary": "query=is:unread label:invoices",
  "result": "success",
  "duration_ms": 420,
  "details": { "matched_count": 7 },
  "trace_parent": "cron-20260428T143000Z-a3f21b",
  "log_version": 1
}
```

| Field | Type | Required | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `timestamp` | ISO-8601 UTC | yes | RFC 3339 with millisecond precision |
| `correlation_id` | string | yes | Set by `gen_correlation_id` at trigger time; flows through entire wake |
| `agent_id` | string | yes | kebab-case; matches `agents/<id>/` folder |
| `wake_id` | string | yes | One per wake invocation |
| `action` | enum | yes | `tool_call` / `wake_start` / `wake_end` / `approval_request` / `approval_response` / `escalation` / `kill_switch_fire` |
| `tool` | string | conditional | Required when `action == "tool_call"` |
| `args_summary` | string | conditional | Single-line redacted summary of tool args; NEVER full args |
| `result` | enum | yes | `success` / `failure` / `blocked` / `pending` / `denied` / `timeout` |
| `duration_ms` | int | yes | Wall-clock duration of the action |
| `details` | object | optional | Action-specific structured payload |
| `trace_parent` | string | yes | For nested calls; usually equals `correlation_id` at top level |
| `log_version` | int | yes | Currently `1`; bump on schema change |

## File layout

```
.agentbloc/logs/
└── <YYYY-MM-DD>/
    ├── audit.jsonl           # All tool calls
    ├── approvals.jsonl       # action=approval_request|approval_response only
    ├── escalations.jsonl     # action=escalation only
    └── kill-switch.jsonl     # action=kill_switch_fire only
```

Per-day rotation. Logs older than `{{retention_days}}` days are
pruned by `runtime/reference-impl/log-rotate.sh` (run nightly).

## PII redaction

Before emitting any log line, run the args / details through
`scripts/pii-redact.sh` (or runtime equivalent). The redactor:

1. Strips email addresses → `<email-redacted>`
2. Strips phone numbers (E.164 + national formats) → `<phone-redacted>`
3. Strips IBAN / credit-card / national-ID patterns → `<pii-redacted>`
4. Strips long alphanumeric strings (likely tokens) → `<token-redacted>`
5. Redacts free-text fields > 200 chars → first-100-chars + `[truncated]`

If a domain has additional PII patterns (medical record numbers,
SSN-equivalents), extend the redactor. The build session adds team-
specific patterns to `governance/pii-redaction.md`.

## What NEVER appears in logs

- Full email bodies (only metadata: sender, subject hash, date)
- Bank account numbers (only last 4 digits)
- Authentication tokens or API keys (redacted to `<token-redacted>`)
- File contents over 200 chars (truncated)
- Approval reasoning that contains user PII (redacted before append)

## Retention + rotation

| Log type | Retention | Rotation |
|---|---|---|
| audit.jsonl | {{retention_days}} days | Daily |
| approvals.jsonl | {{approval_retention_days}} days | Daily |
| escalations.jsonl | {{escalation_retention_days}} days | Daily |
| kill-switch.jsonl | indefinite | Daily |

Compliance posture (GDPR Article 30): retain for the period required
by the user's regulatory regime; longer retention requires legal review
because logs (even redacted) can constitute "processing".

## Tests the build session writes

Assert on log shape AT MINIMUM:

1. Every tool call produces exactly one `tool_call` line
2. Every wake produces exactly one `wake_start` and one `wake_end`
3. `correlation_id` is non-empty + matches `gen_correlation_id` format
4. `args_summary` contains no email / IBAN / token patterns
5. `log_version` matches the current schema version
6. JSON parses (one object per line, newline-delimited)

Reference impl's `tests/` directory has fixtures for these.

